World Cup organisers and Fifa are under pressure after TV viewers spotted hundreds of empty seats at opening games that were supposed to be sold out. 

Except for the opening game between Brazil and Croatia, most matches have been played in unfilled stadiums.

Switzerland played Ecuador on Sunday in the Arena Brasilia which as a capacity of 72,500 but it appeared to be only two-thirds full.

