Reports claim many fans were still outside waiting when the match kicked off.

However, Fifa said the official figure of those in attendance was 68,351. 

Meanwhile, those watching at home spotted hundreds of empty seats during the Spain Netherlands match on Friday and England versus Italy on Saturday.

With just hours to go before the Argentina and Bosnia Herzegovina kick-off on Sunday night at the Maracana stadium, tickets were still available online priced at £80.  

Tickets to see Bosnia Herzegovina play Iran in Salvador next week which cost £110 remain largely unsold.

